Web?topicID=464.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hmmmm... I wonder...[Pet Heal AA for mages?]</span><hr size=1> Why do we not get critical heals on our pets?  Why wouldn't we get a special aa skill that would allow that to happen, like the way we do critical dd spells now.  As far as I know, all other classes that can heal and cast dd are able to do crits on both sides of the board.  I don't think it would be game changing or unbalancing, and would love the chance to do a crit heal on good ol' jobober--he needs it every now and again.  What do you think?<br>
