 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A> at: 2/8/03 4:22:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhasinfirestorm@themagicianstower>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1277<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 7:25:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmmm... I wonder...</span><hr size=1> Because, while we're highly proficient summoners and conjurers of cheap tricks (Hi Gandolf!), we are not adept at healing. If we were, our heals would be standard recast time, not 7ish seconds. Besides, we can crit nuke for upwards of 4.5k. Small price to pay in sacrificing crit heals to do our primary calling (ie: laying out a serious beatdown with the Elemental A Team!) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886&quot;"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ninjacorp.com/Rhasin_sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doomteddy>Doomteddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 9:43:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmmm... I wonder...</span><hr size=1> I was wondering about the same thing. I dunno why they excluded Magicians to have healing gift for pets heal..<br>
<br>
I play my beastlord, and got him the healing gift and adept trained, and pet heal do get crit healed ( double of its value, which is handy sometimes )<br>
<br>
Now, on the other hand, Mages have MGB for just 1 group spell, the DMG shield buff, Beastlords do not have MGB, and have multiple group buffs, which could benefit them.<br>
<br>
One thing I know, Beastlord got the best pet heal than any other pet class in the game,  Mage and Necro got the very close ties on pet heals now with PoP spells.<br>
<br>
So, Beastlords do not have MGB, Magicians do not have Healing Gift, but does have dmg nuke crit aaxp.<br>
<br>
Finally, all I can say is, it's either some advantages and disadvantages that Mages can have while cannot have what Beastlords have, vice versa for Beastlord cannot have what Mages have.<br>
<br>
Alas, I wouldnt mind seeing Mages get healing gift to help keeping the pet alive and Beastlords have the MGB for group buffs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-Doomteddy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 381<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 10:37:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/armiture/eq/artulyn-tag.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmmmm... I wonder...</span><hr size=1> Well if we don't specialize in healing and therefore shouldn't get healing adept, then clerics shouldn't be getting Spell Casting Fury as they are not experts in nuking. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p>&lt;Crispin' Critters for Mithaniel Marr since 29MY1999&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mysite.verizon.net/res0qqnm/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/artulyn-sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
&lt;Political Correctness is Intellectual Fascism&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swagman@themagicianstower>swagman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 1:36:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   healing pets</span><hr size=1> I have heard alot about increasing the mage's abilities to heal pets. I dont think people that scream for better abilities to heal pets have a good grasp on the magician class. We are summoners not cleric. If our pets die when summon a new one for the cost 1 gp, usually more then made up for by the loot the mob drops that we kill. Dont get attached to your pet, like its your pet poodle Fido. Its not. its there to bleed for you and die.  Think of it as any other spell. when it is spend cast it again and again like a nuke, until the mob is dead.  You pet is there to deal damage but more importantly to keep the mob of you. It really is nothing more then a root DOT spell so use it like one.<br>
<br>
Now there are times that you need a fully buffed, fully armed pet. But the situations that we need that kind of pet is few and far between. In group setting and in situations that your pet can mow down the mobs like butter is about the only time when this kind  of pet is appropriate.<br>
<br>
One final consideration about making us better at healing our pets. It would severly over balance our class. Mages are the best soloest in the game hands down. Mages are not the most powerful soloing class in the game, but they are the best. In fact, of the accepted soloing classes mages are probably the weakest. That may sound like a contradiction, but is not. And this is why Mages are the easiest, quickest and most efficient killing machines in the game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=napsilan>napsilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 1:46:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> pallies get spell casting fury...do they even have damage spells? <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=329840"><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/napsilan/flysig.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2864<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 4:21:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> Mages are not priests, healing is at best a secondary ability.  Healing AA, except for those involving <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mend Companion</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, are probably not appropriate for mages.<br>
<br>
Clerics and wizards have pets, yet they do not have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Pet Discipline</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Our healing ability is clearly bounded by that of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Beast Lords</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which are semi-priestly.<br>
<br>
Mages are properly an offensive class.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balphasar>Balphasar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 4:45:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> What I think is funny is that we have mass group buff.  I wish that they would tune the AA's to the class some.  For example:  If you have mass group buff but the only thing you can buff lasts 10 minutes, then have mass group buff recycle once every 10-15 mins. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalahadbb>KalahadBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 5:32:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure Mages are the only class with any form of healing spell that do not get the healing AA's.  Why?  Say we're not healers all you want.  Melees all get casting crits soley for their procs, why?  They are not casters.  Heck even necros get healing crits and they deal with death not healing.  I sent a feedback in about this months ago, dunno why we don't get them =/. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=526560" target="top"> Arch Convoker Kalahad Thundersoul</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ringofvalor.com">Ring of Valor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2868<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 8:55:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I'm pretty sure Mages are the only class with any form of healing spell that do not get the healing AA's.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->What about the other casting class that heals: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Necromancers</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?  I bet they do not get any heal AAs.  Bards have happy healing songs, do they?<br>
<br>
Everyone that gets heal AAs is either a priest class, which obviously specializes in healing, a priest-melee hybrid such as Ranger or Paladin, whose parent class specializes in healing, or Beastlords, which are neither fish nor fowl.<br>
<br>
Healing is an incidental ability of mages, a concession to practical necessity, and by no stretch of the imagination an area mages specialize in.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 829<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 9:43:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> One of the problems with this discussion is that EQ's spell casting abilities (conjuration, divination, alteration, evocation) don't always mesh well with the types of spells being cast.<br>
<br>
Since our high level healing spells are Conjuration based, by that definition alone, we should have some additional boost to the ability (beyond specialization). We're resummoning part of the elemental that has been lost.<br>
<br>
If all our heals were all alteration based, I'd agree, we shouldn't receive any kind of bonus. Right now, since low level heals are alteration based, they should be clumsy and ineffective.<br>
<br>
But as long as our main high level heals are in the conjuration realm, we should be as effective at casting them as any other class in the game. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 58th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balphasar>Balphasar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(2/9/03 2:29:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=464.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: healing pets</span><hr size=1> The thing is that our heals SHOULD have been alteration based.  However, in order to attempt to get the mage community to use them they made them conjure based.<br>
<br>
